<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910918-0040</DOCNO><DOCID>910918-0040.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Villeroy andamp; Boch AG:   Profit Fell 15% in 1st Half   Despite a 5.2% Gain in Sales</HL><DATE>09/18/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   G.VAB</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)GERMANY (GE)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Villeroy andamp; Boch AG, a German porcelain and tile maker,reported that pretax profit fell 15% in the first halfdespite a 5.2% gain in sales.   Pretax profit fell to 50.9 million marks ($30.4 million)from 60 million marks, while sales rose to 811.8 millionmarks from 771.6 million marks.</LP><TEXT>   Net profit fell 15% to 22 million marks from 26 millionmarks.   Villeroy andamp; Boch blamed the decline in profit on a weakperformance by its tiles division, where sales didn't matchyear-earlier levels. The second quarter was better than thefirst, however, and the company said it expects a small salesgain by the end of the year.   Villeroy andamp; Boch's overall sales were propped up bybusiness in Germany, counterbalancing further deteriorationin export markets. The company said sales in Germany rose3.7%, compared with a 2.4% drop in France, a 0.6% declineelsewhere in Europe and a 0.7% decline in the rest of theworld.   The company predicted that its dividends for the yearwould remain flat at last year's levels, 9 marks ($5.38) forcommon shares and 10 marks for preferred.</TEXT></DOC>